	<presentation id="culture">
		<title short="API Culture">How to Establish an Effective API Culture</title>
		<toc class="abstract">The most valuable as well as challenging aspects of using APIs are not just about technology. One such aspect is the organizational aspect, which looks at how API strategy needs to be aligned with team structures so that teams can create and deliver the self-contained and reusable capabilities that APIs make accessible. Another such aspect is the business aspect, which looks at how a faster-paced world means that organizations must become better at adapting to changing environments. This presentation looks at what it takes to make the most out of APIs. What does your organization need to do so that APIs can become the change agent that they are supposed to be?</toc>
		<toc class="resources"><a href="https://nordicapis.com/five-common-misconceptions-about-apis/" title='Erik Wilde, "Five Common Misconceptions About APIs", Nordic APIs, March 2020'>API Misconceptions</a>&#160;· <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/reverse-engineering-organization-gregor-hohpe/" title='Gregor Hohpe, "Reverse Engineering the Organization", May 2018'>Reverse Engineering the Organization</a></toc>
