	<presentation id="strategy">
		<title>API Strategy, Programs, and Platforms</title>
		<toc class="abstract">APIs are essential for both digital transformation of organizations and for participating in the digital economy. While these goals may seem different, the most effective way for organizations to adopt APIs is to see them as two sides of the same coin. An API strategy should cover all uses of APIs, both for private APIs for internal purposes, and for partner and public APIs for externally-facing purposes. An API program should be planned and executed to cover all these API scenarios, so that APIs can be planned, designed, implemented, discovered, and used coherently. One important part of the API program is to establish an API platform that becomes the foundation of digital resources and capabilities within the organization. This presentation looks at how these different pieces of strategy, program, and platform fit together, and what the deciding factors are when it comes to making sure that APIs are used in an effective and productive manner.</toc>
